we dye in the Lord; Every man while he lives, Pſal. hath many Troubles, ſayes holy David; even the Righteous; Every one, when he dyes, hath not many, hath not any Comforts; For ſome are tormented in Hell, ſayes holy Abraham; But the Righteous have many Comforts, ſayes holy Iſaiah;
Iſa. 31.17. The work of Righteouſneſs ſhall be Peace; The End of Righteouſneſs ſhall be Quietneſs and Aſſurance for ever.

